        <p>Concentrates in immune cells at 10-100x plasma levels. Supports neutrophil migration, phagocytosis, and microbial killing. Cochrane review: 14% reduction in cold duration in children with daily supplementation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Zinc: immune development</strong>
        <p>Required for T-cell maturation, NK cell activity, and cytokine production. Zinc deficiency impairs both innate and adaptive immunity. Meta-analysis: reduced cold duration by 1-2 days when supplemented within 24 hours of symptom onset.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Vitamin D3: immune gene regulation</strong>
        <p>Regulates 200+ immune-related genes. Activates antimicrobial peptides (cathelicidins, defensins) in respiratory epithelium. Meta-analysis: 20% reduction in respiratory infection risk in deficient children.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Elderberry: antiviral support</strong>
        <p>Anthocyanins inhibit viral replication in laboratory studies. A 2004 study showed elderberry extract reduced cold duration from 6 days to 3.1 days. Safe in processed form for ages 2+.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

